rComments: It was a previllege to have Paul Adjei Banahene as my TA for Equity Studies. But for him, I would not have been able to pass this course. His explanation of the concepts is second to none. When he mounted the stage during some of the lectures and begun to lecture, I told myself,wow, Paul is a great lecturer. He is definately a great prof for U of T
Paul is an amazing TA - He'd make a great professor. Absolutely loved his passion and teaching style.

NEW444H1S - Nonviolence & Social Change: Paul is brilliant & passionate about the topics discussed. He explains theory w/ vivid examples. Expects a lot and you will see it in his marking. Come exam time, just bring it all. Cover your bases w/ clear & complete answers. The course isn't easy but you can get a good mark. Ask & he will help you there.
I attended Paul's tutorials on Equity studies and I never needed to go to the lectures. The best TA ever! can make a good prof.

TA for Intro to Equity: Paul gives the greatest explainations & examples for the most complex concepts I've ever experienced. By far the best TA I have ever had. Seriously committed to equity and his students. Paul is perfect for audio visual learners because his descriptions are picturesqe and highly memorable. He will be an amazing prof!
